column5: anyone know any good spots to do some shorefishing for bass in or around Barrie, Ontario??
even though I never tried it while I lived there, I imagine the whole Barrie shoreline could produce smallmouth. Lots of rocky breakwalls.
Park on the Lake shore and take a walk.Your bound to see others fishing .You never know what you could catch !

I've caught a couple nice smallies from shore on the Barrie waterfront. I usually go to the north-east portion of the park (where the shore runs north-south), and you can cast out toward the bay. Have had decent luck just chucking tubes and working them back to shore.
